<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 14 at 6:56AM EST  by NWS Binghamton</headline>
<description>...SNOW SQUALLS LIKELY TODAY...
A potent arctic cold front today will likely produce strong snow
showers with even potential for snow squalls. The main window of
opportunity for any snow squalls will be mainly from 9 AM to 2 PM
today. During any snow squalls, brief whiteout conditions are
possible due to the combinations of falling snow and windy
conditions. Snow amounts of an inch or locally 2 inches will be
possible in the squalls. Southwest wind gusts will likely reach
up to 40 to 50 mph today, especially in or just behind the
squall. Temperatures fall through the 20s and into the 10s by late
afternoon or evening.</description>
